<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-08T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-08T09:00:00-05:00" n="583" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/42:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-08T15:00:00+01:00">September
                                    8, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1844. Your circular September 4, 2 p.m. Competent French military
                            authorities have informed our Military Attaché that they are glad to
                            authorize the officers on the staffs of our Military and Naval Attaches
                            at Paris to inspect promptly by personal [apparent omission] the scene
                            of any bombing of a non-military objective in France. (According to the
                            staff officer with whom Military Attaché talked, General Gamelin had
                            endorsed “<hi rend="italic">tres bien</hi>” on this order.)</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>